Auto Scaling in AWS

What is Auto Scaling?

Automatically add or remove resources based on demand

Traffic (inc) -> add servers

Traffic (dec) -> removing servers


EC2 Auto Scaling

Core Components of Auto Scaling

• Launch Template

Blueprint for EC2 instances

Contains

▪ AMI

▪ Instance type

▪ Security group


• Auto Scaling Group (ASG)

Group of EC2 instances managed together

Key Settings

▪ Min instances

▪ Max instances

▪ Desired Capacity


• Scaling Policies

Rules for Scaling

Types

▪ Target Tracking

Keep CPU at 50%

▪ Step Scaling

CPU > 70% -> add 1 instance

CPU > 75% -> add 2 instances

▪ Scheduled Scaling

Scale at specific time


