Application Load Balancer vs Network Load Balancer


ALB:

User -> ALB -> decides based on URL -> Server

Smart Routing (HTTP level)

Best for

• Web applications

• Microservices

• Rest APIs


NLB:

User -> NLB -> forwards based on IP/Port -> Server

Fast routing (Network level)

Best for

• Ultra high performance

• Low Latency

• Supports TCP/UDP

• Static IP support


VPC (Virtual Private Cloud)

A VPC is your own private network inside AWS

VPC = Your isolated network in the Cloud

• VPC is a regional service (make a selection of region)


Q: Can a VPC spans across multiple AWS Regions?

No


Q: Can a VPC spans across multiple Availability zones ?

An Amazon VPC is created at regional level, so it can span across multiple AZs within that region.


Default VPC (in AWS)

A Default VPC is a ready-made virtual network that AWS automatically creates for you in each region when you setup your AWS account

Default VPC: pre-configured network so you can launch resources instantly without setup


Q: Can a default VPC suitable for everything?

It’s great for learning and quick setup but not for production use. A Default VPC in AWS is designed for convenience, not security and scalability


Where Default VPC becomes a bad choice


Security Issue

• All subnets are public
 
• Instances can direct internet access

• Not aligned with best practice (no isolation)


No proper Architecture

• No separation of

▪ Web layer

▪ App layer

▪ Database layer

• No Private subnets


Limited Scalability and Control

• Hard to design:

▪ Multi-tier architecture

▪ Fine-grained routing

▪ Network segmentation


Compliance Problems

• Many organizations require:

▪ Private networks

▪ Strict firewall rules

• Default VPC doesn’t meet these standards


Core Components of VPC


CIDR (Classless Interdomain Routing) Block

IP address assignment scheme. Range of IP addresses for VPC


Subnets

Smaller network inside VPC

▪ Public Subnet

Has internet access

▪ Private Subnet

No direct internet


Internet Gateway (IGW)

Enables internet access


Route Table

Rules for traffic routing


NAT (Network Address Translation) Gateway

Allows private subnets to access internet


Security Groups

Instance-level firewall


Network ACL (NACL)

Subnet-level firewall


Architecture Flow

VPC

|------ Public Subnet -> Internet via IGW

|------ Private Subnet -> Internet via NAT


